INSERT INTO `fn_posts` VALUES (1736, 1, '2015-03-23 20:18:10', '2015-03-23 20:18:10', '<h2>Objective</h2>\r\nChoosing any topic and any design style, create an informational site.\r\n<h2>Implementation</h2>\r\nI''d been seeing a lot of single-page long-scrolling sites being used for start-ups, designers, <a href="http://www.spelltower.com/" target="_blank">products</a>... etc. and thought it would be a good fit. My wife was 7 months pregnant at the time, so we were talking a lot about education, and how we wanted to raise our child, so the topic of immersion education was an easy choice.\r\n\r\nFrom a design side, I wanted to work with bold colors. I naturally am pretty conservative with colors, so I wanted to stretch myself that way.\r\n\r\nI chose a system where each section of content would have its own color background, and re-used those colors for the text and graphics of the other sections to create some consistency and uniformity when the backgrounds are so different.\r\n\r\nFrom a coding standpoint, it''s a very simple site. Just one page with jump links on an nav fixed to the top of the page. I did learn how to create the full-width element with a nested centered element, which was very satisfying.\r\n<h2>What I would do differently now</h2>\r\nIt''s a static site, so I would make it responsive. I would also take a look at the nav and see if it makes more sense somewhere else. I think it''s a little distracting on the top. Also given it''s strctural simplicity, I could look at beefing up the content and adding more interactive elements like animations.', 'Long-scrolling informational site', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'long-scrolling-informational-site', '', '', '2015-03-23 21:46:03', '2015-03-23 21:46:03', '', 0, 'http://www.frank-nelson.com//?post_type=project&#038;p=1736', 0, 'project', '', 0);
